> Thanks @timyuer , but the Kafka still fails at first time after kerberos enabled if I only have ZooKeeper and Kafka installed

@kevinw66 Thanks for your review. This is because the old ephemeral node in zookeeper is not expired (**In the same path the new ephemeral node sessionId is different from the old ephemeral node**) and the new ephemeral node cannot registered.  
It has no relation with this PR, and it should be fixed by the next PR.

@brahmareddybattula 
I think it is good to go.
Could you check on this?

After apply this PR, the cluster was successful created by blueprint.
